users.uswest.net/~abaker3/images/Riah60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Mystefied</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">As a 29th level mage I can now summon coldstones.  Coldstone necklaces are a no rent summoned item that grant ultravision to the user and can either be worn around the neck or carried in the ammo slot.  They don't require any upkeep and can't be debuffed.  In my opinion they are great items.<br>
<br>
Upon reaching 29th level, I was fully prepared to deal with other adventurers asking me to summon coldstones for them.  I mean, who doesn't want ultravision (well, those dark elves who already have ultravision <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
<br>
Much to my surprise I have only received a few requests for coldstones.  And even more surprising, when I take the time to give them away (standing in a safe location and shouting that I'm giving away coldstones) I rarely have any takers.<br>
<br>
Why aren't coldstones in high demand?<br>
<br>
Just last night I ran across a lower level group.  I asked them if anyone would like a free coldstone.  A dwarf replied that he didn't need one because he had infravision.  Is infravision better than ultravision?<br>
<br>
/em is puzzled<br>
</font><P><center>
